Reasoning: The paper focuses on improving the effectiveness of convolutional networks in producing discriminative features, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed Gaussian-based softmax function is a novel approach to achieving this goal, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The evaluation of the proposed method on classification datasets and multi-label classification datasets also involves image processing and computer vision techniques, which could be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM).
